cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with object segmentation in microscopy images using a convolutional neural network (CNN) based deep learning architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of multi-resolution deconvolution filters and extra convolutional layers, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and machine learning, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of publicly available datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
